.TH "ida_alloc_range" 9 "ida_alloc_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ida_alloc_range \- Allocate an unused ID.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ida_alloc_range
.BI "(struct ida *ida "  ","
.BI "unsigned int min "  ","
.BI "unsigned int max "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ida" 12
IDA handle.
.IP "min" 12
Lowest ID to allocate.
.IP "max" 12
Highest ID to allocate.
.IP "gfp" 12
Memory allocation flags.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate an ID between \fImin\fP and \fImax\fP, inclusive.  The allocated ID will
not exceed INT_MAX, even if \fImax\fP is larger.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Any context. It is safe to call this function without
locking in your code.
.SH "RETURN"
The allocated ID, or -ENOMEM if memory could not be allocated,
or -ENOSPC if there are no free IDs.
